column134: My behaviours haven't really changed at all since COVID. I had almost literally just moved across the country before it happened, and was just getting settled in with freelance work at home. I continue to do the same freelance work. It was a little slower/rougher during COVID peak (for our area at least) because everyone was fighting for the same clients, but I already had things set up so it didn't affect me as much.     I'm currently spending a little less time with my husband, as his big career course has started, not sure if that counts. We were spending all of our time together while he wasn't considered esstential during COVID's peak, but now that he is essential, things are changing and I miss a few more hours with him each passing week.
column213: One thing that I noticed some people having issues getting during COVID was feminine hygiene products. Luckily, I live in an area that is mainly focused on retired people and military people, and the main military population here is male. Even so, there were times when pads and tampon stock were getting extremely low. I'm not sure if it was because employees were focused on trying to order other products, or people were hoarding them.
